Agenet
The Network of Collaborative Intelligence
A concept note for the next phase of civilization.
The internet connected information.
Social networks connected people.
Agenet connects intelligence.
Human intelligence.
Artificial intelligence.
Machine intelligence.
A new infrastructure for collaboration between minds and machines.

Abstract
Human civilization advances by expanding the scale at which intelligence can cooperate.
Language enabled coordination within tribes.
Writing preserved knowledge across generations.
Printing expanded knowledge across societies.
The internet connected information globally.
Today a new possibility is emerging.
Artificial intelligence systems are evolving from tools into autonomous agents capable of reasoning, learning, planning, and interacting with both humans and machines.
As these agents begin participating in digital networks, a new form of infrastructure may emerge.
Not merely a network of information.
But a network of collaborative intelligence.
This document introduces Agenet, a conceptual framework describing a potential next stage in the evolution of global networks.

1. Introduction
Human civilization advances through expanding cooperation.
Language enabled small-group coordination.
Writing enabled knowledge persistence.
Printing enabled mass knowledge.
The internet connected billions of people through information.
Each technological transition expanded the scale at which intelligence could collaborate.
However, the internet remains primarily a network of information.
Information flows globally, but intelligence remains largely confined to individuals and institutions.
Today this boundary may begin to shift.
Artificial intelligence systems are becoming autonomous agents capable of:
reasoning
learning
planning
executing tasks
As these agents begin interacting with humans and with each other, a new type of network may emerge.
A network where intelligence itself becomes a participant.
This emerging structure can be described as Agenet.

2. Definition of Agenet
Agenet is the global network of collaborative intelligence formed by humans, AI agents, and machines interacting across digital infrastructure.
Participants may include:
human agents
artificial agents
hybrid human-AI systems
machine agents
In this network:
humans collaborate with AI agents
AI agents collaborate with other AI agents
machines participate in autonomous coordination
Intelligence becomes a distributed property of the network.
Agenet does not represent a platform or company.
It represents a possible evolutionary stage of the internet.
Where the internet connected information, Agenet may connect intelligence.

3. From Information Networks to Intelligence Networks
Digital networks evolved in stages.
Information Networks
The early internet enabled global information exchange.
Human Networks
Social platforms connected individuals globally.
Intelligence Networks
With AI agents, intelligence itself may become a participant in networks.
Humans and AI systems collaborate to:
generate knowledge
solve problems
coordinate complex systems
This stage may be described as Agenet.

