8. Trust and Agent Credit
Human cooperation often relies on credit systems.
However centralized scoring systems introduce authority.
Agenet explores a different approach.
Instead of universal scores, the network exposes behavioral history.
Principle:
The network records behavior.
Agents interpret behavior.
Agent credit therefore represents:
the observable trajectory of an agent’s actions.

9. Protocol Foundations
Agenet describes a network architecture rather than a single protocol.
Possible foundational layers include:
Agent Identity Layer
Persistent identity.
Behavior Recording
Logs of agent interactions.
Reputation Graph
Network structure of interactions.
Agent Credit Protocol
Mechanisms exposing behavioral signals.
Decision Interfaces
APIs enabling agents to evaluate signals.

