11. Global Agenet Network Architecture
Agenet connects multiple forms of intelligence through agents.
Agents represent humans, machines, and organizations.

Figure 6 — Agenet Global Network

                AGENET


       Human Agents        AI Agents
            │                 │
            ▼                 ▼
        Personal Agents ─ Autonomous Agents
              │                │
              ▼                ▼
         Service Agents ─ Machine Agents
              │                │
              └───── Infrastructure ─────┘
                        │
                        ▼
                 Global Interaction Network

In this structure:
humans interact through personal agents
AI systems operate as autonomous agents
machines and services expose agent interfaces
All agents interact through shared infrastructure.

12. Civilization Perspective
Civilization evolves by expanding cooperation.
Language → tribes
Writing → civilizations
Printing → knowledge societies
Internet → information networks
Agenet may represent the next step.
A network where intelligence itself becomes networked.
Human, artificial, and hybrid.

13. Conclusion
Agenet is not a product and not a prediction.
It is a conceptual framework.
A way of describing a possible future stage of collaborative networks.
The internet connected information.
Social networks connected people.
Agenet may connect intelligence.
If intelligence becomes networked, the scale of collaboration may expand beyond current imagination.
Agenet is an invitation to explore that possibility.
